SOCCER 10 POOL OF THE DAYMonday 4 July S10 V1 Montreal have emerged as frontrunners in the race for Major League Soccer honours this season but a trip to LA Galaxy will provide a good test of their credentials. More details at www.soccer6.co.za. M1 KA Akureyri vs Valur Reykjavik: Valur are two points above KA in the standings in Iceland. Valur have won their past two outings.M2 Arsenal Sarandi vs Estudiantes: Estudiantes have scored 12 goals in winning their last three matches against Arsenal.M3 Aldosivi vs Rosario Central: Aldosivi are bottom of the table in Argentina with a solitary point from their opening five games of the new campaign. Rosario Central have lost three of their past four.M4 Newell’s Old Boys vs Patronato: Newell’s are unbeaten in their past nine clashes against Patronato, winning four of them.M5 Orlando City vs D. C. United: Orlando have won their last two MLS clashes against DC United, who had beaten them three times in a row before that.M6 RB Bragantino vs Botafogo: Both clubs sit in the bottom half of the league in Brazil with 18 points from 14 games. Both were beaten in their last league game last weekend.M7 Independiente vs Platense: Independiente have won four of their past five home games. Platense’s last three outings have all been drawn.M8 Colorado Rapids vs Austin FC: Rapids have a single win in their past five matches. This is the middle game in a three match away stretch for Austin.M9 FC Dallas vs Inter Miami: Dallas have hosted Miami once before, coming from behind to beat them 2-1 two years ago.M10 Los Angeles Galaxy vs CF Montreal: Galaxy have won their last three matches against Montreal, who are among the frontrunners in the MLS Eastern Conference. Suggested permutation: R8.003 x 2,3 x 1,2 x 1 x 1 x 1 x 1 x 1 x 1 ×1